lenders.name: Maggle
lenders.loan_because:
Does it matter why I loan?  I loan because it's the right thing to do and/or because I want to make some small difference in the world and/or because I'm a megalomaniac who gets off on the idea of impacting lives thousands of miles away from myself.  But if you care *why* I loan- if knowing why others loan makes any real difference in how much or to who you contribute- then no matter what my real reasons for lending are, you're automatically worse than I am.  Help however you can for whatever reasons or excuses you want, I truly believe it doesn't matter.  Just help however you can.  Just do it, because otherwise the future is too bleak to contemplate.

There are a 1,000- a million!- people just like me and another how many just like you.  Do you want all those people just like you to sit back and do nothing or do you want them to strive for a better world?

In other words: if you collected every good thing in this world, they might be miniscule or irrelevant in the grand scheme of things, just like an individual  grain of sand.  But the vast deserts of this world are made up of so many tiny grains of sand, and they are great, are they not?

I don't know, I'm tired.  Just help make the world a slightly better place any way you can.  Doesn't matter why.  It'll make an impact, no matter the  "why".
